wikipedia_page.main: Henry David Jones (born 8 March 1989) is an English cricketer.  Jones is a right-handed batsman who bowls right-arm medium pace.  He was born in Kingston-upon-Thames, Greater London and was educated at Caterham School.While studying for his degree at Loughborough University, Jones made his first-class debut for Loughborough UCCE against Gloucestershire in 2008.  He made four further appearances for the team, the last of which came against Hampshire in 2009.  In his five first-class matches, Jones scored 8 runs at an average of 2.66, with a high score of 6 not out.  With the ball, he took 6 wickets at a bowling average of 57.33, with best figures of 4/57.
